texts.text: *Wince*
Hahahaha! Not bad!
We got him down to one knee. Finally.
Yeah, but it took all of us giving it all we got to do it.
So what do you hope to achieve by defeating me?
To become king of a world with even more war?
Hell no.
We gonna put an end to this chaotic world.
We hope to end this world where people impose their will with violence,
and achieve peace!
THAT is your answer? How absurd.
And what means will you use to achieve your foolish goal?
The very violence that you so abhor.
Huh?
Umm...
What's the matter? No retort?
But worry not. You are not the only ones who are at conflict with themselves.
Say what?
Before I manifested here...
I was floating about in the Dragon Stream, where I came in contact with many human thoughts.
There I learned that though you humans say you value a peaceful world of law and order,
it is agonizing to you.
In time you always decide that those laws are repressive and tyrannical, and rise up to defy themâ€•
with lawless violence.
B-But laws that are too restrictive would only cause pain to the people.
If people don't revolt against them, they will just be exploited until they die a meaningless death.
That's why...
You're right. Living under laws that have been imposed upon you by others is hard to bear.
So when people start to feel that their freedom is being infringed upon by those binding laws,
they revolt.
And those who use violence to overthrow law and order are praised for their actions and called heroes.

Umm...
I-I guess...
In the end, what all humans really want deep down is
to have the power to be free from all restraints.
You are no different.
You want to achieve "a world of order and peace".
So you use force. You kill those who oppose you. And now here you are.
You use violence to impose your will upon others who do not share your vision.
Let me ask you, how much Blood Karma have you harvested?
All that Blood Karma, you must have taken a lot of lives to get them.
Blood Karma is Karma in physical form.
It is the physical representation of how much Karma you have amassed from killing others for personal gain.
Karma amassed from... killing others for personal gain...
You demons don't belong to the human world! Neither does this world of yours!
The rules and laws of the human world don't count here!
This is a world where the strong can kill the weak without having to deal with consequences.
How are we suppose to obey the rules when there aren't any? We HAD to use force.
It had to be done, so we can put an end to this world!
So, you mean to say that because your rules and laws don't apply here, you can just do whatever you want?
Is that how your rules work?
The demons you killed, quite a lot of them were originally human you know?
Even so, because they have become demons and the rules don't apply,
that makes it alright to kill them?
That is what you're building your world of peace and order from?
I didn't mean...
Behold this power. It is not mine alone.
It is the power given to me by the many who long for the existence of this world.
It is their will that sustains it, because they approve of this world and the freedom they found here.
It does not discriminate between race and class, human and demon.
This is such a world where anyone can be free to use their power and talent to the full.
That's bullshit!
In a world where you can kill to get your way,
only the strong get to live free!
That I do not deny. Only the strong can live unrestricted in this world.
But here you stand before me, survivors of this lawless world.
No matter how you deny it, you above all others
embody the essence of this world.
I can see it now.
In the war against the gods that is to come,
I see you slaying gods in the name of freedom.
You will do everything in your power to fight, even if it means bending the gods to your will and enslaving them.
I see you at the center of a world of chaos and power.
The world that I pursue.
Therefor, I will not fight you here.
Whoa...?
Because I foresee that when the time comes, you will fight alongside me to defy the gods and their rule.
And I want to see you fight for dominance with violence.
The Liberators aren't interested in that.
Do you truly speak for everyone of you?
What da hell does that mean?
I mean that you will all need time to ponder, if there is any uncertainty.
I will see you in the forthcoming war against the gods.
What kind of world will you create then? I am anxious to find out.
>Asura Lord levitates, and then starts to disappear.
Hang on a sec! We ain't finished talkin'!
Ye the mighty.
Shape the world as you will with your might.
Sonuvabitch! He just shit all over us and ran away!
Umm. The world around us is getting blurry.
Is this normal?
Oh! Right.
Because this world is made out of Blood Karma,
the Asura Lord, having absorbed most of the Blood Karma here,
was really what kept this world intact.
Now that he's gone, this world is starting to fall apart...!
Soon, the spiritual world existing here will disperse, and this place will return to reality.
This world is falling apart?

No... NO!
I don't want to go back!
Here, we were equally judged by our power.
There was no discrimination towards race and sex here.
Nobody ever got persecuted for being different here.
It was fair!
Please, don't take that away from us...
Reality never protected us. Not the schools. Not society.
They just repressed us! They sacrificed us to maintain their order!
There are so many of them. Those that prefer this world to reality...
Mob mentality and social hierarchy...
Discrimination and unacceptance towards people because of their birth, race and status...
It cannot be denied that there are those who suffer from senseless things like that.
And if social order enforces these things rather that protect people from them,
I guess it is only natural to feel anguish.
What is there to be anguished about?

!!
That's... the voice of the Asura Lord?
You will all fight your true fight in the real world now, that is all.
You have grown. You should no longer need a mock world such as this.
Go forth into your own world, and wield your power there.

Fight my true fight...
In the real world...
We have grown...?
Yes! I am strong now!
With my new strength, I will change the world!
>Encouraged by the Asura Lord's words, the people depart one by one
>as the Liberators look on.
>At the Hideout, a few days after the rough fight with the Asura Lord...
It would seem that the commotion with the disappearances is coming to an end.
But then, those who died in that world will never come back.
As for the survivors and those who became demons, who knows what will happen to them.
Case solved, for now. But man, this one really left a bad taste in my mouth...
Yeah...
Megakin, I'm just gonna say it out loud.
What you said to that Asura Lord was right.
I'll say it because even though I was just a merc, I participated in wars just the same.
Sometimes, you just can't have peace without war.
That's why we fought in that world. And that's that.
Aight. Thanks man.
But it's just that...
When we were decidin' on a plan of action in that world, I chose to
kill demons and take their Blood Karma as a solution to the problem. I didn't even hesitate.
I was the one who suggested the plan, you don't have to feel responsible.
Y-Yeah!
We all agreed to that plan, so...
There no need to carry all the burden yourself. We can figure it out together.
We have the power to fight and overcome demons.
That is great power. By using it, we can force our will onto others.
That is why we need to think about how we should use that power.
Together.
Yeah, I hear ya.
Aight, I'm okay now. No time to be depressed when you're the leader.
I know it's somethin' that's gonna take time to figure out.
Hell, there might not even be a right answer to this problem.
But even so, we'll find OUR answer. I can promise you that.
